@jdalton Why? This has nothing at all to do with minifying. This has to do with preventing **completely unnecessary** downloads and saving people's space on disk.
Let's do some math:

Lodash is downloaded 48,000,000 times per week. There are about 3.4 megabytes of unnecessary source files in the Lodash source package. That leaves us with 163,200,000 megabytes of unnecessary downloads **per week.** That's 163.2 TERABYTES of bandwidth every week, or 8.4 PETABYTES of bandwidth every year. Why would you willingly let that pass when you can **so easily** prevent it by simply editing package.json?

