The `fp` wrapper of `require('lodash/fp')` transforms lodash methods into auto-curried immutable iteratee-first data-last methods. That means instead of

``` js
var isEven = function(n) { return n % 2 == 0; };

var array = [1, 2, 3];
_.remove(array, isEven);
// => [2]
console.log(array);
// => [1, 3]
```

it's

``` js
var array = [1, 2, 3];
var removeEven = _.remove(isEven);

removeEven(array);
// => [1, 3]
console.log(array);
// => [1, 2, 3]
```

