In my opinion, if this type of check was added, it should work as a negation of `_.isDate`. However, since `_.isDate` only tests if a value is an instance of `Date`, parsing the actual value would be a breaking change. You could use a mixin instead: 

``` js
function isValidDate(value) {
  return !isNaN(Date.parse(value))
}

_.mixin({ isValidDate: isValidDate });
```

I want to stay out of the validation space for the time being as this can expand to more than just `Date`. I'd like to track interest in this though to see if it's something to tack on to our [roadmap](https://github.com/lodash/lodash/wiki/Roadmap). Until then you can always use `_.runInContext` + `_.mixin`:

``` js
// create a pristine lodash instance
var _ = require('lodash').runInContext();
// mixin validation methods
_.mixin({ isValidDate: function() { ... } });
```

