I can dig your use case but think it puts `_.values` in an odd position next to `_.keys`.
As Jeremy mentioned in the Underscore issue you can use `_.map` like:

``` js
var object = { one: 1, two: 2 };
_.map(['one', 'two', 'one'], function(key) {
  return object[key];
});

