From the documentation for `_.result`:

> If object is falsey, then null is returned.

Your commit removes the check to see if the object parameter is falsey :astonished:, causing the tests to fail. The following does what you're looking to do but without breaking existing functionality:

``` javascript
function result(object, property, args) {
    var value = object ? object[property] : null;
    return isFunction(value) ? value.apply(object, toArray(args)) : value;
}
```

